CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 27, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "Capacity Crowds - A section of the crowd which packed the stands for one of the best turnouts in history of local horse shows. Dr. William D. McClelland, chairman of the Ticket Committee, did a swell job, and Hill City will get a fine return from the enterprise. - Courier Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Group of men and women, many wearing hats and overcoats, in audience at Hunt Armory during horse show
